-- Latvia to Save $132 Million in 2013 Budget, Premier Says
-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 2012-09-25T15:01:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/latvia-to-save-132-million-in-2013-budget-premier-says.html
Latvia’s government approved next
year’s budget with a planned deficit of 1.4 percent of economic
output and will send it to Parliament on Sept. 28, the  Finance
Ministry  said.  The budget estimates total spending at 5.82 billion lati
($10.8 billion) and revenue at 5.66 billion lati, the ministry,
based in the capital, Riga, said today in an e-mailed statement.
The economy will grow 3.7 percent next year, according to the
statement.  The budget gap will fall to 0.8 percent of gross domestic
product in 2014 and 0.3 percent the following year, the ministry
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
